 "text": "\n\nFix: \n\n\u003cvuxml xmlns=\"http://www.vuxml.org/apps/vuxml-1\"\u003e\n   \u003cvuln vid=\"9af82e4a-0e65-4bac-ae1d-a7ab633d1f31\"\u003e\n     \u003ctopic\u003emybb -- MyBB search.php SQL Injection\u003c/topic\u003e\n     \u003caffects\u003e\n       \u003cpackage\u003e\n         \u003cname\u003emybb\u003c/name\u003e\n         \u003crange\u003e\u003ceq\u003e1.4.8\u003c/eq\u003e\u003c/range\u003e\n       \u003c/package\u003e\n     \u003c/affects\u003e\n     \u003cdescription\u003e\n       \u003cbody xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\n         \u003cp\u003eSecurityFocus reports:\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003cblockquote cite=\"http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/36460\"\u003e\n           \u003cp\u003eThe application is\nexposed to an SQL injection issue because it fails to sufficiently\nsanitize user-supplied data in the search.php script before using it\nin an SQL query. MyBB version 1.4.8 is affected.\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n       \u003c/body\u003e\n     \u003c/description\u003e\n     \u003creferences\u003e\n      \u003cbid\u003e36460\u003c/bid\u003e\n      \u003curl\u003ehttp://www.securityfocus.com/bid/36460\u003c/url\u003e\n     \u003c/references\u003e\n     \u003cdates\u003e\n       \u003cdiscovery\u003e2009-09-19\u003c/discovery\u003e\n       \u003centry\u003e2009-09-27\u003c/entry\u003e\n     \u003c/dates\u003e\n   \u003c/vuln\u003e"
